function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> isuppercase(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` higher-order function to create a new array containing only the words that start with a capital letter. The anonymous function `w -> isuppercase(w[1])` checks if the first character of each word `w` is an uppercase letter using the `isuppercase` function. The `filter` function applies this condition to each element of the `words` array and returns a new array containing only the elements for which the condition is true.
